{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"init_(cancellable:)","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","externalID":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolPAAE5init_11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO26DBusObjectManagerClientRefV","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The object must be initialized before any real use after initial"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"construction, either with this function or ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_async_initable_init_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable object"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization the error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the object is not initialized, or initialization returns with an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error, then all operations on the object except "},{"code":"g_object_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are considered to be invalid, and have undefined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behaviour. See the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for more details."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable"},{"text":" can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initialized multiple times, unless the class explicitly documents itself as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"supporting this. Generally, a class’ implementation of "},{"code":"init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can assume"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(and assert) that it will only be called once. Previously, this documentation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recommended all "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" implementations should be idempotent; that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recommendation was relaxed in GLib 2.54.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recommended that the method is idempotent: multiple calls with the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"arguments should return the same results. Only the first call initializes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the object; further calls return the result of the first call."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"One reason why a class might need to support idempotent initialization is if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it is designed to be used via the singleton pattern, with a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObjectClass.constructor"},{"type":"text","text":" that sometimes returns an existing instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In this pattern, a caller would expect to be able to call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the result of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"text":", regardless of whether it is in fact a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerClientRef\/init_(cancellable:)"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusobjectmanagerclientref\/init_(cancellable:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerClientRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerClientRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusObjectManagerServer":{"title":"DBusObjectManagerServer","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusobjectmanagerserver","abstract":[{"code":"GDBusObjectManagerServer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is used to export [iface"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObject","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] instances"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using the standardized"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/dbus.freedesktop.org\/doc\/dbus-specification.html#standard-interfaces-objectmanager"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interface. For example, remote D-Bus clients can get all objects","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and properties in a single call. Additionally, any change in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object hierarchy is broadcast using signals. This means that D-Bus"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"clients can keep caches up to date by only listening to D-Bus"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"signals."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DBusObjectManagerServer","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerServer","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DBusObjectManagerServer","kind":"identifier"}]},"http://dbus.freedesktop.org/doc/dbus-specification.html#standard-interfaces-objectmanager":{"type":"link","title":"org.freedesktop.DBus.ObjectManager","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"org.freedesktop.DBus.ObjectManager","type":"text"}],"identifier":"http:\/\/dbus.freedesktop.org\/doc\/dbus-specification.html#standard-interfaces-objectmanager","url":"http:\/\/dbus.freedesktop.org\/doc\/dbus-specification.html#standard-interfaces-objectmanager"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusObjectManagerClientRef/InitableProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusobjectmanagerclientref\/initableprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"title":"InitableProtocol Implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerClientRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/AsyncInitable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","title":"AsyncInitable","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Initable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initable","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Initable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Initable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either via [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Initable.init"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Initable"}]},"#iface@Gio.Initable#description":{"type":"link","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","url":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","title":"description","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"description"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusObjectManagerClientRef":{"abstract":[{"code":"GDBusObjectManagerClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is used to create, monitor and delete object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"proxies for remote objects exported by a [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerServer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(or any code implementing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/dbus.freedesktop.org\/doc\/dbus-specification.html#standard-interfaces-objectmanager","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"interface).","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DBusObjectManagerClientRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DBusObjectManagerClientRef"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerClientRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusobjectmanagerclientref","title":"DBusObjectManagerClientRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusObjectManagerClientRef/init_(cancellable:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusObjectManagerClientRef\/init_(cancellable:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"init_(cancellable:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusobjectmanagerclientref\/init_(cancellable:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}}}